org.sbrubbles.conditio.restarts

Class Resume<R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbrubbles.conditio.restarts.Resume<R>
  • Type Parameters:
    R - unused, since any result is meant to be ignored.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Function<Restart.Option,R>, Predicate<Restart.Option>, Restart<R>, Restart.Option

    public class Resume<R>
extends Object
implements Restart.Option, Restart<R>
    A restart which indicates that execution may proceed "without" returning a value.

    This is meant for situations where the result of Scope.signal isn't used, and the handler means only to acknowledge the condition (and maybe do a side effect or two), like 

       try(Scope scope = Scopes.create()) {
     scope.handle(Progress.class, (s, ops) -> {
       // do something
       showProgressToUser(s.getCondition().getValue());

       // condition acknowledged; carry on
       return ops.restart(Restarts.resume());
     });

     // note that result of signal() is ignored and thrown away
     scope.signal(new Progress(0.6), new Policies<>(), Restarts.resume());

     // ...
   }

    This class works both as a Restart.Option and a Restart. It stores no state, which means that any one instance is equal to any other. So, for convenience, Restarts provides a pre-built instance.

    See Also:
    Restarts, Scope.notify(Condition, Restart[])
